Create a Dynamic Web Project in Eclipse
Name: HelloSpringWeb
Ensure Target Runtime is 
Apache Tomcat v10.1
Click next
Click Next
Tick on Generate web.xml
Click Finish
Open JEE Perspective if not in it.





Right click the Project 
Configure -> Convert to Maven Project

Give Details:
Group ID : com.springmvc
Artifact ID: HelloSpringWeb
Name: HelloSpringWeb
Packaging: war

Finish




Update pom.xml: add before </project>

<properties>
<maven.compiler.source>21</maven.compiler.source>
<maven.compiler.target>21</maven.compiler.target>
</properties>


<dependencies>
        <!-- Spring MVC -->
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-webmvc</artifactId>
            <version>6.2.8</version>
        </dependency>
        <!-- Jakarta Servlet API -->
        <dependency>
            <groupId>jakarta.servlet</groupId>
            <artifactId>jakarta.servlet-api</artifactId>
            <version>6.0.0</version>
            <scope>provided</scope>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>







